{"title": "Nine yards of freedom: Indian women take to running in saris to break taboos", "tags": "asia", "timestamp": "2023-01-07", "content": "NEW DELHI - Ms Meena Kanvinde is a fitness enthusiast. She loves running through Mumbai\u2019s crowded streets at an easy pace. But for years, she has grappled with one conundrum \u2013 derisive stares from passers-by.\nThis is because she runs in a sari, the garment she is most comfortable in. Not body-hugging activewear she feels uneasy wearing."}